♪ Hold steady ♪

1:38:59.273 --> 1:39:01.316
♪ Hold tight ♪

1:39:02.442 --> 1:39:04.987
♪ See where it goes ♪

1:39:06.530 --> 1:39:08.866
That's the funny thing
about forgiveness.

1:39:10.909 --> 1:39:13.370
It does have a stunning,

1:39:13.912 --> 1:39:18.041
one could almost say
magical, effect.

1:39:20.544 --> 1:39:23.046
Who said anything
about forgiveness?

1:39:33.682 --> 1:39:34.850
Oh, Wendy...

1:39:45.402 --> 1:39:46.737
- Hello, parental unit.

1:39:46.820 --> 1:39:48.197
Hello, offspring.

1:39:48.572 --> 1:39:49.740
Would you
like some coffee?

1:39:50.157 --> 1:39:53.535
No, I actually wanted
to borrow something.

1:39:54.745 --> 1:39:55.787
Mm-hm?

1:39:55.954 --> 1:39:57.039
You know...

1:39:57.789 --> 1:39:59.249
that book of yours.

1:40:00.501 --> 1:40:03.003
The one about the rabbit
who goes to rehab.

1:40:04.463 --> 1:40:06.507
Yes, sure. Let me get it.

1:40:07.424 --> 1:40:11.637
♪ And it started out
two hearts, cold ♪

1:40:11.803 --> 1:40:13.514
♪ Kids with nothing to lose ♪

1:40:13.597 --> 1:40:14.765
Who is that?

1:40:14.848 --> 1:40:16.058
What?

1:40:16.433 --> 1:40:17.976
The mysterious lady.

1:40:18.435 --> 1:40:20.103
Oh, her.

1:40:21.855 --> 1:40:23.899
I think you'll want
to meet her.

1:40:26.109 --> 1:40:27.903
She looks kind of familiar.

1:40:28.278 --> 1:40:30.405
And she has quite the story.

1:40:30.906 --> 1:40:32.324
Doesn't everybody?

1:40:32.407 --> 1:40:34.618
Well, hers is long and tangled.

1:40:34.701 --> 1:40:38.288
I mean, they're like
only the best kind.

1:40:39.248 --> 1:40:40.791
Let me get that book for you.

